                <h2 id="week-three">Week Three</h2>
                <p><strong>CSS and HTML5</strong>
                <br>
                 In week three we begin to explore Cascading Style Sheets or CSS for short, and HTML5.
                 HTML5 is the latest version of HTML, which provides stucture and a cleaner look for the page.
                 CSS is where you would enter the code to style the page. You can control the colors, size, layout 
                 and structure of the page. In this section are the Resume Github Pages and Git New Repo.
                </p>

                <h2 id="week-four">Week Four</h2>
                 <p><strong>Forms and More CSS</strong>
                 <br>
                  In week four, we are introduced to more styling methods and the button feature. 
                  The button feature is useful when creating forms for inputting and recording data, for example
                  filling out an application online or signing up for some type of membership. On the CSS side we 
                  explore more styling features like borders and creating themes for webpages. 
                  We also learn about cloud 9 and amazon web services.
                </p>

